        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4853",
        "content": "Indeed I understood that my only hope of deliverance lay in being picked up; and that, though by heading east I should be clinging to the stormy parts, I was more likely to meet with a ship hereabouts than by sailing into the great desolation of the north-west.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
